
            Video
            Japanese young people 'not having sex'
            Japan's youth seem to have gone off sex. According to new research, there are increasing numbers who have never had, or are currently not having, a physical relationship. But is this down to low self esteem or simply not being bothered? The BBC's Tokyo correspondent Rupert Wingfield-Hayes has been trying to find out.
                
                        06 Jul 2017
                    
                
        
